{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require schools to allow students to wear their own clothes at least once a week",
        "additional_details": "I believe this measure would benefit students as I think it would let them be who they want to be and allow them to show their true selves through their choice of clothing. I think it could also be beneficial because I believe it may improve student behaviour.",
        "background": "I call on the Government to require secondary schools to allow students to wear their own clothes at least once a week. I want students to be able to choose what they wear so they can be comfortable and happy. I believe this measure will allow students to express themselves and thrive in school.",
